You can make reactivity progress fast if youre a trainer worth their salt, lowsy trainers take a long time to accomplish little and blame it on the dog. One of the main reasons reactivity takes longer to address is because the dog is going to have to encounter many different types of dogs large, small, intact or neutered, male, female etc.. other reactive dogs and non reactive dogs. But you can start leading your dogs immediately: adequately correct unwanted behaviors and reward good ones.  I’ve trained reactive dogs and fixed the issue in like a week. Harder cases will take a big longer and some dogs I believe have some sort of mental and or hormonal challenges but most of yalls dogs at home are relatively simple fixes humans created. It’s all love at the end of the day we all want what’s best for dogs but have vastly different ways of approaching things. Distracting a dog holding treats by your face or giving them a sniff command when a dog approaches is FAKE LAZY TRAINING IMO.
